arch:property.oc:show_val: Short period of sedimentation following abandonment.
5.50 m north south -by- 1.85 m east west.

Phase X: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.
Brown soil below the collapse (Locus 37) in the southwest room

Locus 41 is the soil below the main collapse (Locus 37) above the floor in the southwest room. It was a fine silt with Munsell 7.5 YR 5/4 (brown). There were generally few inclusions, with some plaster, pottery, and stones, as well as samples of bone, metal, glass, and tesserae. One coin was also found (Seq. No. 106274). The lack of collapse in this locus, and its position just above the floor of the room lead us to phase it as part of a period of sedimentation (Stage 5) prior to the dumping and collapse in the complex.
